TYPE: Test,
TARGET: control module switch and series wiring,
DESCRIPTION: With power applied, measure voltage at both sides of the control-module switch relative to the power-supply negative. First, measure at the incoming pair from the power supply to confirm ~12 V across them. Then, with the switch closed, measure voltage across the outgoing pair to the load. Also measure continuity (with power off) from the switch output terminals to the load-module input terminals to confirm the switch and associated wiring are not open or high-resistance.,
RESULT: Voltage at the control switch measures about 12 V on the positive side and ~0.36 V on the negative side relative to power-supply negative. The PSU Output Cable (−) itself is at 0 V relative to ground. Continuity testing shows the switch output is open to Load Input Cable (+) but has a low-resistance path (1.5 Ω) to Load Input Cable (−).
